exorbitancy.d:
n. A going out of or beyond the usual or due limit;
   hence, enormity; extravagance; gross deviation from rule, right, or
   propriety; as, the exorbitances of the tongue or of deportment;
   exorbitance of demands.

experientialism.d:
n. The doctrine that experience, either that
   ourselves or of others, is the test or criterion of general knowledge;
   -- opposed to intuitionists.

explodent.d:
n. An instrument or agent causing explosion; an exploder;
   also, an explosive.
n. See Explosive, n., 2.

exposures.d:
n. vulnerability to the elements; to the action of heat or cold or wind or rain; 
n. the act of subjecting someone to an influencing experience
n. the disclosure of something secret
